# DDD Advanced Patterns

Integration patterns for complex distributed systems.

## Advanced Elements
- CQRS (Command/Query Segregation)
- Event Sourcing (Sequence of Events)
- Outbox Pattern (Transactional messaging)
- ACL (Anti-Corruption Layer)

## Workflow
1. Use ACL for external integrations
2. Apply Outbox for DB-Message consistency
3. Consider CQRS for high-load query side
4. Use Event Sourcing for auditability

## Anti-Patterns
- Premature CQRS
- Massive Granular Events
